title: Tsa throughput
caption: Comparison between 2019 and subsequent years' 7-day rolling average TSA throughput within 1 January, 2020 and 1 January, 2022 outbound Austin-Bergstrom Intl, Austin, TX.
insights: Average TSA throughput before March, 2020 was 13.0% higher than that in 2019.
Following the onset of the pandemic in the city, a drastic drop in traffic was observed between mid-March and mid-April 2020 and reached as low as -98.0.
The general trend since the mid-April has been a slow but steady increase in TSA throughput and by 1 January, 2022 traffic was 62.0% points greater than the lowest point before mid-April.

In 2020, Periods surrounding holidays such as 4 July (Independence Day), 1 September (Labor Day), 27 November (Thanksgiving) and 25 - 31 December (Christmas and New Year) experienced local spikes in  TSA throughput but never rose to the levels that had been observed in 2019.
